Class AutonomicController

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.upmc.components.AbstractComponent
      • fr.upmc.autonomicController.AutonomicController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutonomicControllerManagementI, fr.upmc.components.ComponentI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.ComponentImplementedI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.OfferedI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.RequiredI, RequestDispatcherStateDataConsumerI, java.rmi.Remote

    public class AutonomicController
extends fr.upmc.components.AbstractComponent
implements AutonomicControllerManagementI, RequestDispatcherStateDataConsumerI
    The class AutonomicController implements a component that check and do adaptations at regular intervals to assure the good work of the data center.

    Description

    The Autonomic Controller (AC) component simulates the execution of a data center by receiving informations from Request Dispatcher about the requests's execution time. Then he check if the different elements of the data center needs adaptations and make these adaptations. 
     invariant      true
